<br>
I tried the XP when it first came out, and I absolutely hated it.  First, activation SUCKS!  Whoever said it is the AOL of Microsoft OSs hit the nail on the head. I will say that it is a &quot;pretty&quot; OS (my wife loves it), but I don't get nearly the same performance and stability of 2000 Pro.  I also hate the way it has been &quot;dumbed down&quot;.  The only thing that I did like about it was the increased compatibility with some of my older games that won't run on 2000.  Of course they run great on the 98SE machine.  I don't even touch the drive anymore except to fix whatever my wife broke.<br>
<br>
Of all the releases throughout the years, I would say that NT was the best and most stable, followed by 2000 Pro, and ME was the absolute worse.  YMMV.<br>
<br>
Also, for security you might consider a modular hard drive.  Check startech.com or your favorite pc gear store for removable hard disk drawers.  Simply take the hard drive out when you leave and lock it up. <p><div align="center"> <a href="#"><img src="http://www.nemeandesign.net/eq/sig2.jpg" width="382" height="66" border="0" onClick="window.open('http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=528641', 'morillion', 'WIDTH=800,HEIGHT=600')"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arothtb>Aroth TB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 2:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8834.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  .</span><hr size=1> 2000&gt;&gt;XP<br>
