<br>
Buy removable hard drive kit. It is a set of rails and a quick plug so you can pop out your hard drive when you leave.<br>
<br>
They, if very dedicated, can buy their own hard drive and load it to use with your computer, but it wont impact your data. <br>
<br>
Bios PW - Pop out the battery and reset it. Situation solved.<br>
Windows PS- During boot, can go into alternate boot modes and bypass it.  <br>
3rd party software- During boot, can use a system boot disk, drop to c prompt uninstall software or edit the windows ini files to disable it.<br>
<br>
Also, Passwords are one more thing you have to deal with on your side, and they are a pain in the ass.  Pull the drive, put it somewhere locked or hidden, and you are 100% safe every time.<br>
<br>
